{title: If You Can't Give Me Love}
{artist: Suzi Quatro}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[A] Well, I've seen[A] you before on that discotheque floor
You were [Bm]driving me out of my mind
Oh, but I[D] could have sworn that I saw something more in your eyes[A]
Oh, though you were surrounded by beauty unbounded
Your [Bm]glance is intended for me
And though I[D] tried to hide it, I found myself lookin' to see[A]
So, then you took your chances, you made your advances
Your [Bm]touch took my breath away
But when you[D] said, "Hello, are you ready to go?"
Well, [A]I had just one thing [E]to say
{end_of_verse}


{start_of_part: Pre-Chorus}
If you can't[Bm]  give me love[E]
